{"name": "Altra Olympus 4 Trail Running Shoes - Men's", "categories": ["Home", "All", "Run and fitness", "Running and training footwear", "Running shoes", "Trail running shoes", "Olympus 4 Trail Running Shoes"], "description": "Plush cushioning to tackle long distances over challenging terrain. The Olympus 4 features an ample toe box that allows your toes to spread and splay naturally during your foot strike, and zero drop that promotes a natural stride. A rounded heel promotes a smoother step from heel to toe.Engineered knit upper is durable and breathable.Gaiter trap helps to secure a range of trail running gaiters.Wide toe box accommodates natural spreading and splaying at the moment of foot strike.A-Bound recycled EVA midsole provides maximum cushioning.Inner Flex grooves cut weight.Vibram\u00ae MegaGrip outsole offers great traction in rugged terrain.\n\n        Sustainability\n\n\n\n\n\n.st0{stroke:#333;stroke-width:.79;stroke-miterlimit:10}\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                      Recycled content", "product_code": "6010-307", "tech_specs": {"Weight": ["658g (9)"], "Ideal for": ["Trail running"], "Feel\n\n'Minimal and natural' shoes offer low drop, lots of flex, and minimal cushioning. Most running shoes are 'Light and responsive' with medium cushioning and good energy return. 'Cushioned and floaty' shoes have maximum cushioning.": ["Cushioned and floaty"], "Stability\n\nSome shoes include added motion control or stability features to help minimize over pronation, where the foot tends to roll inward in a biomechanically imbalanced running position.": ["Neutral"], "Upper material": ["Synthetic", "Mesh"], "Closure": ["Lace-up"], "Heel-to-toe cushioning\n\nThe approximate thickness of the midsole cushioning under the heel and the forefoot. A thicker heel and greater difference between heel and toe height tends to suit heel-strike runners, while forefoot and midfoot strikers may prefer a minimal drop between heel and toe cushioning.": ["33-33mm"], "Drop\n\nThe drop is the difference in height between the heel and the forefoot midsole cushioning. Traditional running shoes tend to have a 10mm drop or higher while minimalist style shoes are on the lower end of the spectrum.": ["0mm"], "Waterproof\n\nWaterproof shoes and boots feature a waterproof-breathable membrane and a gusseted tongue to help keep your feet dry in wet conditions.": ["No"], "Removable insole": ["Yes"], "Product sustainability": ["Recycled content"], "Made in": ["China"]}, "img_urls": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9192818475038/6010307-BK151.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193694724126/6010307-BK151-ALT-A.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193694789662/6010307-BK151-ALT-B.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193695051806/6010307-BK151-ALT-C.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9192818475038/6010307-BK151.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193694724126/6010307-BK151-ALT-A.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193694789662/6010307-BK151-ALT-B.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9193695051806/6010307-BK151-ALT-C.jpg"]}